HEADWORD: Monday
<hw>Mon"day</hw> <pr>(m⟦ucr⟧n"d⟦asl⟧; 48)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>moneday</ets>, <ets>monenday</ets>, AS. <ets>m⟦omac⟧nandaeg</ets>,
i.e., day of the moon, day sacred to the moon; akin to D.
<ets>maandag</ets>, G. <ets>montag</ets>, OHG. <ets>m⟦amac⟧natag</ets>,
Icel. <ets>m⟦amac⟧nadagr</ets>, Dan. <ets>mandag</ets>, Sw.
<ets>m⟦aring⟧ndag</ets>. See <er>Moon</er>, and <er>Day</er>.]</ety>
<def>The second day of the week; the day following Sunday.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

